cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NI, cs.SI

This paper is about website fingerprinting attacks and defenses, which are related to computer security (cs.CR). The paper proposes a new attack that leverages convolutional neural networks (cs.LG) for better accuracy. The use of deep learning also suggests the paper may belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The attack is evaluated against Tor, which is a network protocol (cs.NI), and the paper discusses the need for more robust defenses, which could fall under the systems and information theory (cs.SI) sub-category.
